# Frontend Standards (apps/web)

## API layer

- Use **apisauce** (`@/lib/api/apisauce`) for HTTP — not raw `fetch` in components.
- Use **TanStack React Query** for reads (`useQuery`) and writes (`useMutation`).
- Put query keys in `@/lib/api/query-keys.ts`; put hooks in `@/hooks/api/`.
- Map apisauce failures to `ApiError` via `parseApiResponse`.

## Forms

- Use **react-hook-form** + **@hookform/resolvers/yup** for all user-facing forms.
- Disable native HTML validation (`noValidate` on `<form>`).
- Show field errors with `@/components/ui/form/field-error` under the input.
- Use shared fields: `TextField`, `PasswordField`, `CheckboxField` from `@/components/ui/form`.

## Feedback

- Use **sonner** toasts (`toast.success`, `toast.error`) for API/auth outcomes.

## Reusable components

Prefer `@/components/ui/*` before one-off markup. Use `Brand`, `Button`, `MsIcon` for consistent UI.

## Feature folder structure

Each screen/feature lives in its own folder under `components/sections/`:

```
dashboard/
  DashboardContainer.tsx   # hook: useDashboard() — logic only, no JSX
  DashboardComponents.tsx  # presentational sub-components
  Dashboard.tsx            # screen UI — composes components + hook
  types.ts
  constants.ts
  index.ts
```

- **`*Container.tsx`** — state, handlers, form setup. Returns typed props. **No JSX.**
- **`*Components.tsx`** — presentational pieces. Props in, JSX out.
- **`Feature.tsx`** — calls container hook, composes components.
- **`app/.../page.tsx`** — layout/metadata/redirect guards only. Renders `<Feature />`.

## Buttons

Use `@/components/ui/button` with variants: `primary`, `secondary`, `destructive`, `ghost`.

## Brand

- Wordmark: Newsreader serif + `.ai` in violet (`#5B3DF5`)
- UI sans: Inter; headings: Plus Jakarta Sans
- Logo mark: lowercase `l` SVG in `@/components/ui/logo-mark.tsx`
